    "---\n",
    "## 1. Data Loading\n",
    "\n",
    "Our dataset consists of real `.eml` files — raw email messages in standard Internet Message Format (RFC 2822).\n",
    "\n",
    "### The `parse_eml_folder` function\n",
    "This function:\n",
    "1. Iterates over all `.eml` files in a folder (sorted for reproducibility)\n",
    "2. Opens each file with `errors='ignore'` to handle encoding issues gracefully\n",
    "3. Extracts the body — handling both **multipart** emails (which have attachments/HTML/text parts) and **simple single-part** emails\n",
    "4. Returns a **pandas DataFrame** with one row per email\n",
    "\n",
    "### Labeling\n",
    "The `X-Spam-Status` header contains the spam flag set by the mail server.\n",
    "- **1** = spam (header starts with 'Yes')\n",
    "- **0** = ham (legitimate email)\n",
    "\n",
    "We apply this directly to both train and test sets to create our target variable `label`."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "cell-load",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def parse_eml_folder(folder_path):\n",
    "    \"\"\"Parse all .eml files in a folder into a pandas DataFrame.\"\"\"\n",
    "    records = []\n",
    "    for filename in sorted(os.listdir(folder_path)):\n",
    "        if not filename.endswith('.eml'):\n",
    "            continue\n",
    "        with open(os.path.join(folder_path, filename), 'r', errors='ignore') as f:\n",
    "            msg = email.message_from_file(f)\n",
    "\n",
    "        body = ''\n",
    "        if msg.is_multipart():\n",
    "            for part in msg.walk():\n",
    "                if part.get_content_type() == 'text/plain':\n",
    "                    body = part.get_payload(decode=True).decode(errors='ignore')\n",
    "                    break\n",
    "        else:\n",
    "            body = msg.get_payload(decode=True).decode(errors='ignore')\n",
    "\n",
    "        records.append({\n",
    "            'filename':    filename,\n",
    "            'subject':     msg.get('Subject', ''),\n",
    "            'sender':      msg.get('From', ''),\n",
    "            'body':        body,\n",
    "            'spam_status': msg.get('X-Spam-Status', '')\n",
    "        })\n",
    "    return pd.DataFrame(records)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Update these paths to point to your dataset location\n",
    "train_df = parse_eml_folder(os.path.expanduser('~/Downloads/TRAINING'))\n",
    "test_df  = parse_eml_folder(os.path.expanduser('~/Downloads/TESTING'))\n",
    "\n",
    "# Create binary label: 1 = spam, 0 = ham\n",
    "train_df['label'] = train_df['spam_status'].str.startswith('Yes').astype(int)\n",
    "test_df['label']  = test_df['spam_status'].str.startswith('Yes').astype(int)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(train_df.shape, test_df.shape)\n",
    "train_df.head()"
   ]
