    "---\n",
    "## 6. Decision Tree Classifier (Baseline)\n",
    "\n",
    "### What is a Decision Tree?\n",
    "A Decision Tree is a flowchart-like model that splits data at each node based on the feature that best separates the classes:\n",
    "1. Finds the word and threshold that best splits the data (minimizing Gini impurity)\n",
    "2. Recursively splits each resulting subset\n",
    "3. Stops when a stopping criterion is met (max depth, min samples, etc.)\n",
    "\n",
    "### Strengths & Weaknesses\n",
    "| Pros | Cons |\n",
    "|------|------|\n",
    "| Highly interpretable | Prone to overfitting |\n",
    "| No feature scaling needed | High variance |\n",
    "| Fast to train | Sensitive to small data changes |\n",
    "\n",
    "### Cross-Validation\n",
    "We use **5-fold cross-validation** for a reliable performance estimate. The training data is split into 5 equal parts; the model trains on 4 parts and validates on the 5th, rotating through all combinations. This gives 5 accuracy scores — we report the mean ± standard deviation."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "cell-dt1",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Train baseline Decision Tree\n",
    "dt_clf = DecisionTreeClassifier(random_state=42)\n",
    "dt_clf.fit(X_train_tfidf, y_train)\n",
    "y_pred_dt = dt_clf.predict(X_test_tfidf)\n",
    "\n",
    "print('=== Decision Tree (Baseline) ===')\n",
    "print(f'Test Accuracy: {accuracy_score(y_test, y_pred_dt):.4f}')\n",
    "print('\\nClassification Report:')\n",
    "print(classification_report(y_test, y_pred_dt))"
   ]
